The paper proposes a tool that supports identification and action on bias in visual news media, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning (ML) algorithms for bias identification, which falls under the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of bots to engage people in conversation about bias, which involves multimedia (cs.MM) techniques.
